Eric,
I have a patch set available for kexec for 2.5.68.  I have checked it on
the 3 different systems (listed below), and all worked as expected.
There were no changes, and the previous version of kexec-tools worked
without modification.
The patches are available for download from OSDL's patch lifecycle
manager ( 
http://www.osdl.org/cgi-bin/plm/
 ).
Patch stack for kexec for 2.5.68:
        kexec base for 2.5.68:
        
http://www.osdl.org/cgi-bin/plm?module=patch_info&patch_id=1790
        kexec hwfixes for 2.5.68:
        
http://www.osdl.org/cgi-bin/plm?module=patch_info&patch_id=1791
        kexec usemm change (allowed 2-way to work for me):
        
http://www.osdl.org/cgi-bin/plm?module=patch_info&patch_id=1792
        optional change to defconfig (sets CONFIG_KEXEC=y):
        
http://www.osdl.org/cgi-bin/plm?module=patch_info&patch_id=1793
The patches are also available (with matching kexec-tools-1.8) from this
link pending a crontab update:
http://www.osdl.org/archive/andyp/kexec/2.5.68/
Regards,
Andy
